<AST/><BRK/>
<NPR>NOTE:  A long term alternate power supply is almost never required by the control system itself, this will usually 
be required (if at all) by tenant requirements or by the overall system design and should seldom be added as an 
ad-hoc requirement.  Control systems for underlying systems with alternate power should use that alternate power 
source.</NPR><BRK/>
<BRK/>
<NPR>A UPS may be desired for specific control system components where rapid recovery after a power outage is required, 
or where the control system itself is necessary for restoration of power.  Again, this should be driven by mission 
requirements and control system specifications should already require adequate system restoration after loss of power.<BRK/>
